I'm assuming this is a Roslyn issue, rather than a Visual Studio issue.  Let me know if this should be filed elsewhere, or if more information is needed.

## Issue description
When a namespace is updated, either through moving files around in the Solution Explorer and Visual Studio prompting to update namespaces, or through the ` "Change namespace to match folder structure"` quick action, it will remove remove unnecessary parentheses added for clarity, even if `dotnet_style_parentheses_in_other_binary_operators ` is set to `always_for_clarity` (the default).

I should add that there is _no_ `IDE0047` message reported, and in any case I wouldn't expect a namespace update to run code formatting/cleanup operations beyond the adjustment of the `namespace` line and the potential removal of a `using` directive if it matches the new namespace.

For example, consider the following code:
```csharp
    internal class Class1
    {
        private bool Condition1 { get; }
        private bool Condition2 { get; }
        private bool Condition3 { get; }

        public void Method1()
        {
            if ((Condition1 && Condition2) || Condition3)
            { }
        }
    }
```

When dragging the file containing that code to a new folder and choosing `"Yes"` on the `"Adjust namespaces for moved files"` dialog (or, if the file is in a folder structure that doesn't match the namespaces, running the quick-action `"Change namespace to match folder structure"`), the `if` condition will have the parentheses in the first part removed, becoming `if (Condition1 && Condition2 || Condition3)`.

## Steps to Reproduce
The project that reproduces the issue can be found [here](https://github.com/Metritutus/ParenthesesNamespaceAdjustmentIssue001).

1) Open `Class1.cs` (in order to directly observe the change).
2) Drag `Class1.cs` into the `Namespace1` folder.
3) Click `Yes` on the `"Adjust namespaces for moved files"` prompt.
4) Observe that the conditional expression in `Class1.cs` has changed.

### Expected Behavior
Only the namespace in `Class1.cs` is altered.

### Actual Behavior
The namespace and the `if` condition in `Class1.cs` are both altered.

## Additional information
**OS version**: Windows 11 Version 22H2 (OS Build 22621.1992)
**Visual Studio version**: 17.6.5
